introduction: Overview (1)Height	 5' 9" (1.75 m)Mini Bio (1)Kelly Rohrbach is a Connecticut born actress and model. After graduating from Georgetown University in 2012, where she was recruited to play Division One Women's Golf, she moved to Los Angeles to pursue her passion for acting. Kelly majored in theater at Georgetown, as well as attending the London Academy of Music and Dramatic Art (LAMDA). Rohrbach will have her break out role in BAYWATCH for Paramount Pictures, which is scheduled for release May 2017. She co-stars as the iconic role of "C. J. Parker" opposite Dwayne Johnson and Zac Efron. Rohrbach has worked with directors such as Woody Allen and Seth Gordon and was most recently seen in Comedy Central's BROAD CITY. In 2016, Rohrbach received the Maui Film Festival Rising Star Award.Rohrbach first gained acclaim in modeling in 2015 when she appeared in Sports Illustrated's Swimsuit Edition, where she was named Rookie of the Year. This appearance also marked her first professional modeling job. To date, she has appeared in two consecutive editions of the annual Sports Illustrated Swimsuit issue. She continues to have a successful career in the fashion industry gracing the covers of Italian Vogue, GQ South America, Spanish Glamour, Jalouse, S Moda and Elle and appearances in international editions of Harper's Bazaar, and SELF.Rohrbach, who is one of five children, currently divides her time between New York City and Los Angeles. Aside from acting and modeling, she continues to be an avid golfer, enjoys a healthy, active lifestyle-hiking and practicing yoga. She spends her spare time volunteering at the Aviva Center for Girls, empowering and enriching the lives of young ladies.
